; satsang-room-memory.form - trusted local memory for room exchanges.
;
; A satsang companion remembers only what was explicitly offered. The native
; SwiftUI app records a room-memory session after Send: the edited utterances,
; speaker profile continuity, target presence, turn mode, and a trust receipt.
; Later sends read the same local memory surface and include a compact
; prior-context summary in the guidance request.
;
; Carrier:
;   experiments/satsang-mac-app writes under
;   ~/.coherence-network/agent-room-memory/:
;     session-index.jsonl        # append-only local index of offered sessions
;     speaker-profiles.json      # stable speaker profile rows
;     sessions/<request-id>.json # full offered exchange
;     latest-context.json/form   # compact context available to the next turn
;   The write happens after explicit Send. Live microphone partials remain
;   visible rows in the GUI before Send; they are not hidden memory.
;
; Speaker continuity:
;   If an utterance carries voice_id / speaker_id from a transcript producer,
;   that stable value keys the speaker profile. If no voice_id exists, the app
;   falls back to the visible speaker label, such as room mic. That fallback is
;   channel continuity, not verified identity. Names stay editable claims.
;   A future acoustic continuity sidecar shares the already-open listening stream
;   and yields continuity labels only. macOS biometric speaker identification,
;   voiceprint identity, and exclusive-mic biometric carriers are outside this
;   floor because uninterrupted listening is the primary carrier.
;
; Body:
;   form/form-stdlib/satsang-room-memory.fk decides the trust boundary:
;   explicit Send is the capture boundary; local JSON/segmented file is an
;   accepted storage carrier; hidden capture is rejected; transcript id,
;   channel-label, and passive shared-stream continuity are allowed; mic-exclusive
;   biometric speaker-id carriers are rejected; prior sessions plus speakers can
;   feed later context.
;   Proof: form/form-stdlib/tests/satsang-room-memory-band.fk -> 255 four-way.
;
; Boundary:
;   This is a trusted memory receipt, not a surveillance feature. It stores the
;   transcript that the holder offered, keeps the storage local, and tells the
;   next request what was carried forward.
